The 74-year-old spent nearly two months receiving treatment in London for an undisclosed illness earlier this year. JOHANNESBURG Nigeria's President Muhammadu Buhari has made his first public appearance in weeks, re-emerging amid mounting concerns about his health.The 74-year-old spent nearly two months receiving treatment in London for an undisclosed illness earlier this year. News agency AFP is reporting this evening that Buhari was seen at prayers at a mosque in the presidential villa in Abuja earlier on Friday.